@@eThornwood -- As Kowloon Sees It@@N

@@dWardens of Iron, Northern Threat Assessment@@N

Thornwood is a @@rnecrotic estate-forest@@N south of the Great Northern
Forest's canopy edge. That proximity makes it a direct threat to our
southern trade lifeline. The @@yLantern Road@@N passes through the forest.
If Thornwood's expansion reaches the Road, overland commerce @@rdies@@N.

The Wardens study Thornwood as a @@rmilitary threat@@N. The @@rWild Hunt@@N
-- the estate's mobile enforcement arm -- has extended its patrol
range farther toward the Lantern Road than in any prior generation.
Clearing patrols in the @@WNorthern Crown@@N have encountered Hunt-sign:
thorn-scarred trees, bark-textured tracks, root-rot smell. The
interval between sightings is shrinking.

Four logics govern Thornwood, each threatening what Kowloon values.
@@yManorial logic@@N -- gates, titles, hereditary protocol -- corrupts
legitimate governance. @@dFunerary logic@@N -- charnel verges, exhumation
cycles -- treats the dead as material resource. The Temple Circle
condemns this: the dead are @@ynamed and honored@@N, not processed.
@@gForest logic@@N is nature made predatory. And @@lsubstrate logic@@N --
crystalline formations mediating necrotic ecology -- recalls the
@@WConclave's@@N abandoned crystals in the Cinderteeth. @@rInstruments
without keepers become hazards.@@N

Lord Harren was @@rretained@@N by his estate -- awareness trapped in
the system he created. The Jade Magistracy reads this as the ultimate
@@rcautionary tale@@N of authority refusing to acknowledge expired
mandate. The Ashfall taught Kowloon that survival requires
@@yrebuilding@@N, not @@dclinging@@N. Harren clung. The forest ate him.

The @@rRoot Covenant@@N -- blood opening listening channels, roots
carrying memory -- inverts everything the Temple Circle teaches.
Bone remembering debt when ledgers fail is @@rfunerary rite without
proper naming@@N. The Temple Circle calls this @@dthe erasure of the
named@@N.

The @@dThornwood Lich@@N maintains a biological binding that is
@@rfailing@@N. The Wardens read this as escalation: internal stress
expands outward. The Hunt pushes farther because the interior can
no longer contain it.

Kowloon's response: doubled patrols in the Northern Crown, emergency
signal relays on the Lantern Road, overland disruption priced into
contingency ledgers, and the Temple Circle researching @@ycounter-
rites@@N against what prayers alone cannot hold.

@@rThe forest is not coming for us. It is coming for the Road.@@N
That is worse.
